PMAT-512: cuBLAS backward_steps=0 — loss not captured by canary parser

STATUS: FIX SHIPPED (2026-04-06)

ROOT CAUSE:
InstructTrainer::train() in entrenar computed per-epoch train_loss but never
emitted it to stderr. The canary parser reads stderr for loss[=:] patterns.
WGPU path had per-sample + per-epoch eprintln, CUDA path was silent.

FIX (3 changes, 2 repos):
1. entrenar instruct_trainer.rs: eprintln!("  Epoch {} complete: avg_loss={:.4}")
   per epoch + "[training] Training complete: final_loss={:.4}" at end
2. apr-cli finetune.rs: eprintln!("[training] final_loss={:.4}") after trainer.train()
3. Published entrenar 0.7.12 + apr-cli 0.4.16

VERIFICATION:
- cargo install apr-cli → 0.4.16 (confirmed)
- Canary parser regex compatible (tested against new format)
- Needs gx10 re-run to confirm actual loss values captured

